HEADWORD: Isobront
<hw>I"so*bront</hw> <pr>(⟦imac⟧"s⟦osl⟧*br⟦ocr⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Iso-</ets> + Gr. <grk>bronth`</grk> thunder.]</ety>
<fld>(Meteor.)</fld> <def>An imaginary line, or a line on a chart,
marking the simultaneous development of a thunderstorm, as noted by
observing the time when the thunder is heard at different
places.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isocephalism</ent>⟦br⟧
